301
00:18:19,011 --> 00:18:20,480
A little aggressive,huh?

302
00:18:20,499 --> 00:18:22,226
You're doing good.

303
00:18:29,884 --> 00:18:32,034
Okay.

304
00:18:38,291 --> 00:18:40,076
Move as soon as we
got a position on 'em.

305
00:18:40,086 --> 00:18:41,122
Copy.

306
00:18:41,141 --> 00:18:42,283
Gordy,we got ears yet?

307
00:18:42,302 --> 00:18:44,337
Getting an audio signal.

308
00:18:44,769 --> 00:18:47,264
- Please!
- Tell me the truth!

309
00:18:47,628 --> 00:18:50,824
If we could just go outside,please?

310
00:18:50,834 --> 00:18:53,194
You can just talk to your husband.

311
00:18:53,214 --> 00:18:55,229
Please,let me talk to my wife.

312
00:18:55,248 --> 00:18:58,041
Josh,we can't right now. We can't.

313
00:18:58,444 --> 00:18:59,806
Spike's on Less Lethal.

314
00:18:59,826 --> 00:19:01,236
Boss gonna need you with the gas.

315
00:19:01,246 --> 00:19:02,580
What do you mean,"lethal"?

316
00:19:02,609 --> 00:19:04,614
Josh,Plan A is less lethal.

317
00:19:04,643 --> 00:19:05,555
Less lethal?

318
00:19:05,574 --> 00:19:06,917
Rubber bullets.

319
00:19:06,937 --> 00:19:08,635
How can you be less dead?

320
00:19:08,654 --> 00:19:10,708
We dislodge the weapon,
restrain the subject.

321
00:19:10,727 --> 00:19:12,032
This is insane.

322
00:19:12,061 --> 00:19:15,046
You have all this hardware for
an upset woman with maybe a knife.

323
00:19:15,084 --> 00:19:16,255
Knife's as bad as a gun.

324
00:19:16,293 --> 00:19:20,497
It never sticks,never jams, never runs out of ammo
and you don't need traing to know how to use it.

325
00:19:20,506 --> 00:19:23,721
So just sit down and calm yourself.

326
00:19:25,324 --> 00:19:29,671
Please,please, I'm so scared! Please?

327
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:34,843
I've got eyes. Female hostage.
Knife confirmed. Threat imminent.

328
00:19:34,853 --> 00:19:37,703
- Spike,stand by.
- Copy.

329
00:19:38,836 --> 00:19:40,688
On my go.

330
00:19:40,697 --> 00:19:44,747
Please don't hurt me! I'm pregnant!

331
00:19:49,766 --> 00:19:51,110
She's pregnant. Hostage is pregnant.

332
00:19:51,119 --> 00:19:55,994
Stand down! Stand down. Stand
down. We got a pregnant hostage.

333
00:19:56,752 --> 00:19:58,854
You...

334
00:19:59,363 --> 00:20:01,781
you're having his baby?

335
00:20:02,059 --> 00:20:03,950
No.

336
00:20:07,366 --> 00:20:10,053
You're having his baby.

337
00:20:11,665 --> 00:20:14,448
Your having his...

338
00:20:18,949 --> 00:20:22,500
I knew it. I knew that there
was a reason that,that...

339
00:20:22,509 --> 00:20:25,254
why he'd given up. It was you.

340
00:20:25,571 --> 00:20:27,173
Please,you're not making sense.

341
00:20:27,193 --> 00:20:29,064
You're coming with me.

342
00:20:29,074 --> 00:20:31,828
- Please,you need to talk to someone.
- Get up!

343
00:20:31,837 --> 00:20:35,590
Okay,team,new rules: No Taser,no
CS gas and no rubber bullets.

344
00:20:35,609 --> 00:20:37,106
Not a lot of tools in the toolkit.

345
00:20:37,125 --> 00:20:38,267
Gordy,we hear anything yet?

346
00:20:38,296 --> 00:20:39,860
Yeah,it's not clear.

347
00:20:39,889 --> 00:20:41,655
Please! Please!

348
00:20:41,664 --> 00:20:43,747
Go up the stairs.

349
00:20:48,737 --> 00:20:50,205
- They're wrestling.
- Spike?

350
00:20:50,215 --> 00:20:52,038
I've lost them. I've lost visual.

351
00:20:56,011 --> 00:20:57,902
Boss,let me send in
some gas, clear them out.

352
00:20:57,911 --> 00:20:59,379
Negative. She's pregnant.

353
00:20:59,389 --> 00:21:02,057
We got to go in,boss. We got to risk it.

354
00:21:04,005 --> 00:21:06,903
No!

355
00:21:15,694 --> 00:21:17,287
Enough!

356
00:21:17,296 --> 00:21:19,734
Please watch out for the baby!

357
00:21:19,743 --> 00:21:21,634
Enough!

358
00:21:22,056 --> 00:21:27,277
Enough,enough. Enough. Enough.

359
00:21:27,286 --> 00:21:30,290
Please,please don't hurt the baby.

360
00:21:30,933 --> 00:21:34,954
Thank you. Thank you. Thank you.

361
00:21:34,963 --> 00:21:38,754
Come on. Let's go. Upstairs.

362
00:21:38,764 --> 00:21:40,673
I need to show you something.

363
00:21:40,712 --> 00:21:42,785
So you have no idea who this woman is?

364
00:21:43,226 --> 00:21:44,953
No.

365
00:21:44,982 --> 00:21:47,074
Your wife thinks you're
having an affair with her,Josh.

366
00:21:47,084 --> 00:21:50,068
I am,I am not having an affair.

367
00:21:50,078 --> 00:21:52,813
You understand the risk
you're taking if you lie to me?

368
00:21:52,832 --> 00:21:54,521
I love my wife.

369
00:21:54,531 --> 00:21:57,256
We had a tough time, but I love my wife.

370
00:21:57,285 --> 00:22:01,008
I understand that, but what I don't
understand is who she has in that room with her

371
00:22:01,037 --> 00:22:02,611
and why she has a knife to her throat.

372
00:22:02,630 --> 00:22:04,914
Mr. Scott, we need you to draw
a floor plan of your house.

373
00:22:04,953 --> 00:22:06,191
Both floors,Josh.

374
00:22:06,210 --> 00:22:08,830
Every door-- which way
it opens and every window.

375
00:22:08,839 --> 00:22:10,739
- Okay.
- Thank you.

376
00:22:10,749 --> 00:22:12,083
Eddie,Eddie,what's he saying?

377
00:22:12,092 --> 00:22:13,455
That he's not involved with anyone.

378
00:22:13,474 --> 00:22:15,595
- You believe him?
- No.

379
00:22:15,605 --> 00:22:17,802
Okay,she says she wants
the truth,and so do I.

380
00:22:17,822 --> 00:22:20,298
He was saying they were having a fight
this morning, talking about having a baby.

381
00:22:20,307 --> 00:22:23,340
Let's see how that escalated before
this knife starts swinging again.

382
00:22:23,359 --> 00:22:25,211
Lou,I want you to patch
me in on this conversation.

383
00:22:25,230 --> 00:22:26,497
I want Sam and I to hear it.

384
00:22:26,516 --> 00:22:28,474
Copy that.

385
00:22:28,483 --> 00:22:30,153
Sarah,it's Sam.

386
00:22:30,172 --> 00:22:33,195
I'm trying to phone
again. Please pick up.

387
00:22:46,794 --> 00:22:49,126
Did he tell you about this?

388
00:22:50,479 --> 00:22:52,542
What?

389
00:22:53,137 --> 00:22:56,688
About the eight years?

390
00:22:56,697 --> 00:22:59,845
I don't know. I don't
know what you're saying.

391
00:22:59,855 --> 00:23:04,749
Shut up! Over there. Get over there.

392
00:23:06,841 --> 00:23:07,916
Sit down!

393
00:23:07,944 --> 00:23:12,829
I interviewed him for the conference
in New York forWiredmagazine.

394
00:23:13,175 --> 00:23:15,420
We had tea.

395
00:23:15,449 --> 00:23:18,472
That's what I meant by
"yesterday was amazing."

396
00:23:18,491 --> 00:23:22,119
- You're lying.
- The interview... The interview was amazing.

397
00:23:22,128 --> 00:23:25,852
Sarah,I need you to come to the phone
so we can talk about your safety.

398
00:23:34,892 --> 00:23:38,317
- What did you just do?
- Nothing.

399
00:23:38,327 --> 00:23:40,707
- What did you just do?
- Nothing.

400
00:23:41,820 --> 00:23:44,037
We've been trying to have
a baby for eight years.

401
00:23:44,066 --> 00:23:47,242
Eight years of hormone
shots, IVF treatments.

402
00:23:47,281 --> 00:23:50,112
We took out loans. We
drained the accounts.

403
00:23:51,033 --> 00:23:53,413
It looks like we can afford it,right?

404
00:23:53,422 --> 00:23:55,198
But we couldn't.

405
00:23:55,217 --> 00:23:58,259
A year ago we get pregnant, finally.

406
00:23:58,528 --> 00:24:00,390
But we didn't want to tell anyone
because we wanted to be sure.

407
00:24:00,428 --> 00:24:04,228
So we waited-- one
month,two months,three...

408
00:24:04,247 --> 00:24:08,048
At four months,we made this...

409
00:24:08,057 --> 00:24:10,975
we made this room for the baby.

410
00:24:11,675 --> 00:24:14,391
We let ourselves believe.

411
00:24:16,761 --> 00:24:19,467
We told everyone.

412
00:24:19,496 --> 00:24:21,492
And we lost it.

413
00:24:22,308 --> 00:24:23,594
How'd she handle it?

414
00:24:23,613 --> 00:24:25,389
She fought back. She's a fighter.

415
00:24:25,398 --> 00:24:28,546
I didn't want to give up.

416
00:24:30,148 --> 00:24:32,951
For him.

417
00:24:34,160 --> 00:24:36,712
He should be a father.

418
00:24:36,722 --> 00:24:39,150
Is she delusional? Mentally unstable?

419
00:24:39,160 --> 00:24:42,096
No. No,I mean she...

420
00:24:42,106 --> 00:24:44,553
she was depressed for a
while, but she's not deluded.

421
00:24:44,582 --> 00:24:48,497
Then tell me why she thinks you're having
an affair with a total stranger,Josh?

422
00:24:48,507 --> 00:24:50,407
Boss,we're picking up
some kind of audio signal.

423
00:24:50,426 --> 00:24:51,510
What kind of audio signal?

424
00:24:51,530 --> 00:24:53,631
From the house, intercom maybe.

425
00:24:53,650 --> 00:24:54,504
Patch it in.

426
00:24:54,543 --> 00:24:57,259
- Josh,you guys have an intercom at your house?
- No.

427
00:24:57,268 --> 00:25:00,176
Walkie-talkies, anything?
We're picking up voices here.

428
00:25:00,483 --> 00:25:03,448
I mean,we have a baby
monitor, but it wouldn't be on.

429
00:25:03,804 --> 00:25:05,454
Where?

430
00:25:05,473 --> 00:25:06,922
- In the nursery.
- What floor?

431
00:25:06,932 --> 00:25:09,360
It's on the second
floor, front of the house.

432
00:25:09,370 --> 00:25:10,895
Can you get it any clearer,Lou?

433
00:25:10,924 --> 00:25:12,652
I'm working on it.

434
00:25:16,452 --> 00:25:19,456
Okay,team, we know we're not welcome
here, so let's go stealth, low and slow.

435
00:25:19,475 --> 00:25:22,143
Spike and Wordy, I want
you on entry with me. Jules.

436
00:25:22,152 --> 00:25:23,419
My cousin has a baby monitor.

437
00:25:23,438 --> 00:25:26,480
It's a two-way, so the kid can
hear the parents. It's worth a try.

438
00:25:26,490 --> 00:25:27,833
Okay,try to tap into that frequency.

439
00:25:27,862 --> 00:25:29,167
Sam,she's not going
to answer that phone.

440
00:25:29,186 --> 00:25:30,213
We'll try this way in.

441
00:25:30,232 --> 00:25:32,459
Jules,I want you to find a
scorpio position on the roof.

442
00:25:32,478 --> 00:25:35,040
I think I saw a skylight
up there. That'll be Plan B.

443
00:25:36,278 --> 00:25:38,447
And bring a camera pole.

444
00:25:42,439 --> 00:25:46,882
I just need to get through this without
you trying something again. Okay?

445
00:25:47,573 --> 00:25:50,759
Okay,we got ears, and we're
good to talk anytime you say,Sam.

446
00:25:50,779 --> 00:25:51,690
Channel 4.

447
00:25:51,710 --> 00:25:57,112
Good work,Lou. I'm gonna need you on
entry with me, and get the husband's keys.

448
00:26:04,454 --> 00:26:07,381
If you want to get out of here alive,

449
00:26:07,390 --> 00:26:11,526
then you're going to tell
me what happened in New York.

450
00:26:12,380 --> 00:26:17,409
You're going to tell me
why you were there with him.

451
00:26:19,031 --> 00:26:21,660
What happened after tea?

452
00:26:22,313 --> 00:26:24,664
Nothing.

453
00:26:27,342 --> 00:26:30,643
What was so amazing then,hmm?

454
00:26:31,171 --> 00:26:34,011
What do you want me to say?

455
00:26:34,568 --> 00:26:37,523
Huh,what do you want?

456
00:26:37,533 --> 00:26:40,815
I lose either way,right?

457
00:26:41,496 --> 00:26:45,901
What kind of answer do you expect when
you wave a knife in someone's face?

458
00:26:46,986 --> 00:26:51,141
I will know the truth when I hear it.

459
00:26:52,120 --> 00:26:55,047
You're not going to like the truth.

460
00:27:10,372 --> 00:27:11,188
Go,Kira.

461
00:27:11,198 --> 00:27:13,395
License plates coming at you.

462
00:27:13,424 --> 00:27:15,468
All right, let's see what we got.

463
00:27:15,478 --> 00:27:18,443
Josh,you recognize any of these?

464
00:27:22,973 --> 00:27:24,220
Hannah Murray.

465
00:27:24,249 --> 00:27:26,562
Oh,my God.

466
00:27:26,571 --> 00:27:28,961
She rented a car that's parked
down the street. You know her?

467
00:27:28,971 --> 00:27:31,850
She's a reporter from New York.

468
00:27:31,859 --> 00:27:33,423
How do you know her?

469
00:27:33,452 --> 00:27:35,717
Why would she... I
haven't seen her since...

470
00:27:35,727 --> 00:27:37,320
Since when, Josh,since when?

471
00:27:37,329 --> 00:27:39,863
Are you telling me that you
had a thing with this woman?

472
00:27:39,872 --> 00:27:43,183
We got to know,buddy, 'cause if
you did, that changes everything.

473
00:27:43,807 --> 00:27:45,707
I did.

474
00:27:45,726 --> 00:27:48,586
I've known Josh for 18 years.

475
00:27:51,062 --> 00:27:55,764
Before Sarah, we were
friends,really close,

476
00:27:56,417 --> 00:27:58,144
but never more than friends.

477
00:27:58,173 --> 00:28:02,194
From the first moment we met, we
had a connection, you know,like...

478
00:28:04,190 --> 00:28:08,518
a really strong connection like...

479
00:28:09,094 --> 00:28:11,454
the ones you can't really explain.

480
00:28:11,474 --> 00:28:15,706
And we lost touch, and then one
day, I'm in New York in a conference,

481
00:28:15,744 --> 00:28:18,873
and we bump into each other and sh...

482
00:28:19,544 --> 00:28:22,231
she asked me if she could interview me.

483
00:28:22,270 --> 00:28:25,408
Then I'm talking to him face
to face after all these years,

484
00:28:25,417 --> 00:28:30,293
and it's like no time has passed.

485
00:28:30,302 --> 00:28:33,546
Sarah and I were in
this really bad place.

486
00:28:33,910 --> 00:28:37,452
I mean,I don't want blame it
on fertility treatments,but...

487
00:28:37,461 --> 00:28:42,739
He said somewhere in there it was like you two
